    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 is a mechanically sound example of the iconic E46 chassis, optimized for the driving purist. At its heart is the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and high-pressure Double VANOS for a linear torque curve and a visceral 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M-Differential Lock. Significant preventative maintenance has been performed, including rear subframe reinforcement and rod bearing replacement, ensuring the structural and internal integrity of the platform. While the finish shows minor road-going patina, the suspension geometry remains tight and the hydraulic steering rack provides the communicative feedback synonymous with this era of M-engineering. This is a turn-key driver\u2019s car ready for spirited canyon duty.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 11
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
